#: ../../source/news/support/announcing-1.0-eol/index.rst:4
msgid ""
"According to Istio’s `support policy </about/release-cadence/>`_, LTS "
"releases like 1.0 are supported for three months after the next LTS "
"release. Since `1.1 was released on March 19th "
"</news/releases/1.1.x/announcing-1.1/>`_, support for 1.0 will end on "
"June 19th, 2019."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/support/announcing-1.0-eol/index.rst:10
msgid ""
"At that point we will stop back-porting fixes for security issues and "
"critical bugs to 1.0, so we encourage you to upgrade to the latest "
"version of Istio ({{}}). If you don’t do this you may put yourself in the"
" position of having to do a major upgrade on a short timeframe to pick up"
" a critical fix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/support/announcing-1.0-eol/index.rst:16
msgid ""
"We care about you and your clusters, so please be kind to yourself and "
"upgrade."
msgstr ""

